---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SiteNav from '../../components/SiteNav.astro';
import FooterAfs from '../../components/FooterAfs.astro';
import SiteFooter from '../../components/SiteFooter.astro';
import CtaBand from '../../components/CtaBand.astro';
import PageHero from '../../components/PageHero.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Vivid Sydney — Festival Security & Crowd Management | Secure Tours & Travel"
  description="Case study: AFS Group delivered crowd management, access control and VIP guest services across Vivid Sydney precincts — one of Australia's largest public events."
  canonical="https://securetours.com.au/articles/vivid-sydney/"
>

<SiteNav active="articles" />

<PageHero
  ariaLabel="Case study hero"
  crumbs={[
    { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
    { label: 'Articles & Case Studies', href: '/articles/' },
    { label: 'Vivid Sydney' },
  ]}
  label="Case Study · Public Festival Security"
  title="Vivid Sydney"
  sub="Festival security, crowd management and VIP guest services across Sydney's largest annual public event — attracting over three million visitors across 23 nights."
/>

<section class="section" aria-labelledby="case-study-heading">
  <div class="container">

    <div class="case-study-meta">
      <div class="meta-item">
        <div class="meta-item__label">Event</div>
        <div class="meta-item__value">Vivid Sydney</div>
      </div>
      <div class="meta-item">
        <div class="meta-item__label">Type</div>
        <div class="meta-item__value">Public Festival — Lights, Music & Ideas</div>
      </div>
      <div class="meta-item">
        <div class="meta-item__label">Location</div>
        <div class="meta-item__value">Sydney Harbour & CBD Precincts, NSW</div>
      </div>
      <div class="meta-item">
        <div class="meta-item__label">Duration</div>
        <div class="meta-item__value">23 nights (annual)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="meta-item">
        <div class="meta-item__label">Services Provided</div>
        <div class="meta-item__value">Crowd Management · Access Control · VIP Services</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="case-study-body">
      <h2 id="case-study-heading">Background</h2>
      <p>Vivid Sydney is one of Australia's largest public events — a festival of light, music and ideas that transforms Sydney's CBD, harbour foreshore and iconic landmarks across 23 nights each winter. The event draws over three million visitors from across Australia and internationally, making crowd safety, access management and VIP guest coordination a significant operational undertaking.</p>
      <p>AFS Group was engaged to provide security and crowd management support across multiple Vivid Sydney precincts, working alongside event organisers, NSW Police and local authorities to ensure a safe and enjoyable experience for all attendees.</p>

      <h2>The Challenge</h2>
      <p>Vivid Sydney presents a unique security challenge: an open-access public festival with multiple simultaneous light installations, concert venues and public spaces spread across a large urban area. Key challenges included:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Managing crowd flow and density at popular light installations along the Circular Quay foreshore</li>
        <li>Coordinating access control across multiple venue types — from ticketed concerts to free public installations</li>
        <li>Providing VIP guest management for corporate event holders and invited dignitaries attending Vivid events</li>
        <li>Maintaining a security presence that was effective without being intrusive in an open, family-friendly festival environment</li>
        <li>Rapid incident response across dispersed precincts with real-time communication between teams</li>
        <li>Catering to large numbers of international visitors with multilingual communication support</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Our Approach</h2>
      <p>AFS Group deployed licensed crowd controllers and close protection personnel across the key Vivid Sydney precincts, with a dedicated command and communication structure enabling real-time coordination across teams.</p>
      <p>A detailed event risk assessment was completed prior to the festival opening, identifying crowd density thresholds, access point priorities, emergency egress requirements and contingency protocols. This assessment informed staffing allocation and team placement for each night of the festival.</p>
      <p>For corporate and VIP clients attending Vivid Sydney events, dedicated chaperone and concierge teams provided door-to-door guest management — from arrival at Sydney hotels through to venue access and return transport.</p>

      <h2>Services Delivered</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Licensed crowd controller deployment across Circular Quay, The Rocks and Walsh Bay precincts</li>
        <li>Access control and queue management at high-attendance light installations</li>
        <li>VIP and corporate guest management for Vivid Sydney event holders</li>
        <li>Close personal protection for invited dignitaries and high-profile attendees</li>
        <li>Real-time incident monitoring and rapid response coordination</li>
        <li>Multilingual support for international visitors and delegations</li>
        <li>Secure transport coordination for VIP arrivals and departures</li>
        <li>Liaison with NSW Police and event management teams</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Outcomes</h2>
      <div class="outcomes-grid">
        <div class="outcome-item">
          <div class="outcome-item__num">23</div>
          <div class="outcome-item__label">Nights of Operation</div>
        </div>
        <div class="outcome-item">
          <div class="outcome-item__num">3M+</div>
          <div class="outcome-item__label">Event Visitors (annual)</div>
        </div>
        <div class="outcome-item">
          <div class="outcome-item__num">Multi</div>
          <div class="outcome-item__label">Precincts Covered</div>
        </div>
        <div class="outcome-item">
          <div class="outcome-item__num">Zero</div>
          <div class="outcome-item__label">Major Security Incidents</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>AFS Group delivered the engagement without major security incidents across all operational nights. The VIP concierge program received strong feedback from corporate clients, with several event holders retaining AFS Group for subsequent Vivid Sydney engagements.</p>

      <div class="confidentiality-note">
        <strong>Confidentiality:</strong> Client and venue partner identities are protected in this case study. Full references are available to qualified enquirers on request. <a href="/contact/" style="color:var(--navy); font-weight:600; text-decoration:underline;">Contact us</a> to request a reference.
      </div>

      <div class="article-nav">
        <a href="/articles/">← Back to Articles & Case Studies</a>
        <a href="/articles/carriageworks/">Carriageworks Case Study →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<CtaBand
  ariaLabel="Case study CTA"
  title="Planning a Major Event?"
  body="Our team can provide a confidential consultation and tailored proposal for events of any scale — from intimate functions to major public festivals."
  primary={{ label: 'Request a Consultation', href: '/contact/' }}
  outline={{ label: 'View Event Solutions', href: '/event-solutions/' }}
/>

<FooterAfs />
<SiteFooter />

</BaseLayout>
